{"lemma":"فاكِهَةٌ","slug":"فاكِهَةٌ","root":"ف.ك.ه","root_slug":"ف-ك-ه","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ك-ه","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فاكِهَة","root":"فكه","pos":"N","occurrence_count":11},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n34396","n34405"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D9%83%D9%90%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fruit","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"أُحِبُّ أَكْلَ الْفَاكِهَةِ كُلَّ يَوْمٍ.","english":"I love eating fruits every day."},{"text":"مُتَّكِئِينَ فِيهَا يَدْعُونَ فِيهَا بِفَاكِهَةٍ كَثِيرَةٍ وَشَرَابٍ","english":"There they will recline, calling for abundant fruit and drink."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/faː.ki.ha/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n34396","headword_ar":"فاكههُ","root":"fkh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaAkahapN","text_ar":"مُفَاكَهَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He jested,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joked, with him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"indulged in pleasantry with him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA tufaAkiho A^amapF walaAtabulo EalaY A^akamapK","text_ar":"لَا تُفَاكِهْ اَمَةً وَلَاتَبُلْ عَلَى اَكَمَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Jest not thou with a female slave, and make not water upon a hillock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and publish not what is secret of thine affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akm","text_ar":"اكم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, TA.) [See also an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tazan~ada","text_ar":"تَزَنَّدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n34405","headword_ar":"فَاكِهَةٌ","root":"fkh","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fruit, of any kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"things, the eating whereof is enjoyed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figs"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"melons"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raisins"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pomegranates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [the words, of the Kur lv. 68,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhimaA faAkihapN wanaxolN warum~aAnN","text_ar":"فِيهِمَا فَاكِهَةٌ وَنَخْلٌ وَرُمَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"have caused it to be much and vainly disputed whether dates and pomegranates be, or be not, included among the things termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAkhp","text_ar":"فاكهة"},{"kind":"text","text":": it seems to be the general opinion of the lexicologists that they are included; but the contrary opinion is held by many of the lawyers, and by the Imám Aboo- Haneefeh among them:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAkihu","text_ar":"فَوَاكِهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kinds thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b2-  And (by way of comparison [thereto], TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sweetmeat;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalowaA='","text_ar":"حَلْوَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) which is also applied by some to “ fruit ” ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fAkhp","text_ar":"فاكهة"},{"kind":"text","text":"), (T in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlw","text_ar":"حلو"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or to “ sweet fruit. ” (K in that art.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAkihapu Al$~itaA='i","text_ar":"فَاكِهَةُ الشِّتَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fruit of winter"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is metonymically used as meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 594.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}